15/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The war crimes court in Belgrade convicted four former paramilitary members Monday (March 14th) of killing civilians during the 1991-1995 war in Croatia. 
Cedo Budisavljevic, Mirko Malinovic, Milan Bogunovic and Bogdan Grujicic were sentenced to 12 years in prison each. 
They were found guilty of killing the five-member Rakic family in 1991, in the locality of Licki Osik. 
(Beta, B92 - 14/03/11)
